~ start
Samuel: O love, how they do hypnotize,\nTwo lanterns at the harbor's edge,\nTwo moons suspended in the skies\nAbove the water, near the sedge.
Samuel: I am the vessel, you the tide,\nI am the shore, you are the sea,\nAnd no man lives who could have priced\nThe hold your eyes have placed on me.
Samuel: Your eyes, my greatest prize,\nMy compass, anchor, northern star,\nThrough morning mist and evening's guise\nI find you, near and yet so far.
Samuel: Do not wanton, do not play\nWith those twin flames that light the dark—\nFor I have given you my days,\nAnd you have kept them, every spark.
=> END